00:13:54,471 --> 00:13:57,951
- you are gone.
- I will not let you down.

244
00:14:00,711 --> 00:14:11,711
Motion carried.

245
00:14:11,711 --> 00:14:13,671
Ho ho ho!

246
00:14:13,751 --> 00:14:16,511
Boys, boys, save it
for the stables, will you?

247
00:14:18,271 --> 00:14:19,951
Look there. They got a new roof.

248
00:14:20,031 --> 00:14:21,071
Easy, easy!

249
00:14:22,031 --> 00:14:23,710
Uncle Scott is here!

250
00:14:25,031 --> 00:14:27,231
Lucy! Coat!

251
00:14:30,271 --> 00:14:31,551
Comet!

252
00:14:31,631 --> 00:14:34,711
Next time we fly, go easy
on the alfalfa, will you?

253
00:14:36,831 --> 00:14:39,350
- Uncle Scott.
- Hey, Luce. There we are.

254
00:14:40,271 --> 00:14:41,871
- There it is.
- All warm?

255
00:14:41,950 --> 00:14:45,191
Just like magic.
You have the warmest hug in the world.

256
00:14:45,271 --> 00:14:48,191
- Hello.
- Hi, Comet!

257
00:14:48,270 --> 00:14:50,231
- Hey, son.
- Hi, Dad.

258
00:14:50,310 --> 00:14:52,630
I missed you so much. Hi.

259
00:14:53,391 --> 00:14:56,671
A few days early, aren't you?
Isn't that baby due any moment?

260
00:14:56,750 --> 00:14:59,630
Oh, we got lots
to talk about. Hey, Neil.

261
00:14:59,711 --> 00:15:02,631
That's a...
That's a good-looking sweater vest.

262
00:15:02,711 --> 00:15:04,751
- It's reversible.
- Of course it is.

263
00:15:04,830 --> 00:15:07,151
- Let's go inside.
- Lucy, come on.

264
00:15:13,031 --> 00:15:15,031
Look at that,
it's snowing in Hawaii.

265
00:15:15,111 --> 00:15:18,030
Yeah. It's not really magical
like the one Charlie has,

266
00:15:18,111 --> 00:15:21,551
but I love it.
And now I have 12. See?

267
00:15:23,070 --> 00:15:26,871
You know, I have
quite the snow globe collection myself.

268
00:15:28,751 --> 00:15:30,431
- How's Danielle doing?
- Good.

269
00:15:30,510 --> 00:15:33,110
Thanks for letting me
go snowboarding with her.

270
00:15:33,191 --> 00:15:36,670
You're welcome.
Hey, I brought you something.

271
00:15:36,751 --> 00:15:39,710
Just a little thing.
Oh, boy.

272
00:15:39,830 --> 00:15:41,470
What a mess in here.

273
00:15:50,510 --> 00:15:53,311
There we are.

274
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:56,191
Wedged behind a wheelbarrow.

275
00:15:56,270 --> 00:15:57,950
Dad! That's awesome!

276
00:15:58,070 --> 00:16:00,510
- Thank goodness it wasn't a car.
- Thanks, Dad.

277
00:16:00,631 --> 00:16:02,310
Wow, this is beautiful.

278
00:16:02,430 --> 00:16:04,471
Lucy, sweetheart,
what are you doing?

279
00:16:04,591 --> 00:16:06,231
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

280
00:16:06,351 --> 00:16:08,431
Come on out. Come out here. Come here.

281
00:16:08,510 --> 00:16:11,031
- Get out of the bag.
- Why can't I fit inside?

282
00:16:11,110 --> 00:16:12,511
It takes a lot of practice.

283
00:16:12,590 --> 00:16:15,111
I wish I could come
to the North Pole with you.

284
00:16:15,190 --> 00:16:17,390
I could help Carol a lot
and she loves me.

285
00:16:17,471 --> 00:16:20,071
That's true. And hey,

286
00:16:20,150 --> 00:16:23,710
maybe I should be the one
there for Carol.

287
00:16:23,791 --> 00:16:25,750
You know?
I mean, another mom.

288
00:16:25,831 --> 00:16:27,751
I could... I could help.

289
00:16:27,830 --> 00:16:30,550
- Hey, maybe...
- Girls.

290
00:16:30,631 --> 00:16:33,791
I've got a full sleigh.
You understand my situation.

291
00:16:33,870 --> 00:16:36,030
Now, wait a minute, Scott.

292
00:16:36,111 --> 00:16:37,950
Let's pause a moment here...

293
00:16:38,031 --> 00:16:40,550
...and take a feelings inventory.

294
00:16:45,270 --> 00:16:49,630
Let's look at what you're doing as
an uncle from a therapeutic standpoint.

295
00:16:49,711 --> 00:16:51,191
Charlie's been to the Pole.

296
00:16:51,270 --> 00:16:53,431
Your new baby's
being born at the Pole.

297
00:16:53,510 --> 00:16:56,190
Lucy's a member of
this family too, Scott.

298
00:16:56,271 --> 00:17:00,350
And if you harshly exclude her
from this formative experience,

299
00:17:00,430 --> 00:17:02,471
you could scar her for life.

300
00:17:02,550 --> 00:17:04,710
And, consequently, her parents,

301
00:17:04,791 --> 00:17:07,910
who must accompany her
on long-distance journeys.

302
00:17:09,830 --> 00:17:11,990
Please, Uncle Scott.

303
00:17:13,590 --> 00:17:15,830
Can I come to the North Pole, too?

304
00:17:20,951 --> 00:17:23,190
Please?

305
00:18:00,751 --> 00:18:03,751
Oh, that's awfully good, isn't it?

306
00:18:05,190 --> 00:18:07,390
Guys, I've done it.

307
00:18:13,310 --> 00:18:16,111
What have you done?

308
00:18:16,190 --> 00:18:20,231
Is it going to clean itself up?
I don't think so. Quickly, quickly.

309
00:18:22,470 --> 00:18:26,030
Curtis, I haven't seen
the bearded wonder around for a while.

310
00:18:26,111 --> 00:18:28,470
- Where'd he go?
- None of your skis' wax.

311
00:18:28,550 --> 00:18:33,030
No need to be nippy. With all
the stress, I wouldn't blame the guy

312
00:18:33,111 --> 00:18:35,950
- for doing that escape hatch thing.
- Escape Clause.

313
00:18:36,030 --> 00:18:38,230
<i>Little elf woman, one cocoa, por favor.

314
00:18:38,311 --> 00:18:40,150
- Right away.
- Thank you.

315
00:18:40,231 --> 00:18:42,550
How does that Escape Clause work,
anyway?

316
00:18:42,630 --> 00:18:45,230
Sorry, classified.
Elfland Security Act.

317
00:18:45,311 --> 00:18:47,631
- That's just what I'd say.
- What?

318
00:18:47,710 --> 00:18:50,270
If I didn't know anything.

319
00:18:51,310 --> 00:18:53,710
Don't be embarrassed.
Makes perfect sense,

320
00:18:53,790 --> 00:18:55,710
big guy would know important stuff.

321
00:18:55,790 --> 00:18:58,230
For your information,
I'm elf number one.

322
00:18:58,310 --> 00:19:00,870
I know all there is
about the Hall of Snow Globes.

323
00:19:00,951 --> 00:19:05,110
Everybody knows about the Hall
of Snow Globes. That's not special.

324
00:19:05,870 --> 00:19:07,190
Not special?

325
00:19:08,911 --> 00:19:11,590
Not special?
It's the most top-secret,

326
00:19:11,670 --> 00:19:14,070
hush-hush, amazing
place in the world.

327
00:19:14,150 --> 00:19:18,070
It's where every Santa through history
has kept his personal snow globe.

328
00:19:18,150 --> 00:19:20,950
How can you say that
that's not special?

329
00:19:21,030 --> 00:19:22,190
Because it isn't.

330
00:19:22,270 --> 00:19:26,150
Unless you know what it has to do with
the Escape Clause, which you don't.

331
00:19:27,110 --> 00:19:29,510
I bet Santa doesn't even trust you.

332
00:19:30,990 --> 00:19:33,870
Now, you listen here, frostface.

333
00:19:34,950 --> 00:19:37,830
Secret Santa snow globe.
Santa.

334
00:19:41,070 --> 00:19:44,030
I wish that I had never
become Santa at all.

335
00:19:48,230 --> 00:19:49,950
Wait, wait, wait, what's this?

336
00:19:50,070 --> 00:19:52,511
This is where I'm transported
through time

337
00:19:52,630 --> 00:19:54,990
and everything goes back
to the way it was,

338
00:19:55,070 --> 00:19:57,790
like I'd never become Santa at all.

339
00:20:00,710 --> 00:20:02,510
Gets the snow globe,

340
00:20:02,630 --> 00:20:05,190
puts his hands on it, says the words,

341
00:20:05,310 --> 00:20:07,070
and then whoosh!

342
00:20:07,150 --> 00:20:08,870
Job opening: Santa Claus.

343
00:20:08,950 --> 00:20:10,470
Told you I know everything.

344
00:20:11,430 --> 00:20:12,630
Wow.

345
00:20:12,710 --> 00:20:16,870
I never dreamed I'd be so well-connected
to elves in high places.

346
00:20:16,950 --> 00:20:19,990
We really must party
in my condo in Gstaad sometime.

347
00:20:20,070 --> 00:20:21,390
It'd be fun.

348
00:20:21,470 --> 00:20:25,430
Tell me, how do you get into
the Hall of Snow Globes, anyway?

349
00:20:25,510 --> 00:20:28,150
Sorry, Jack. Now that's classified.

350
00:20:28,230 --> 00:20:29,670
I know that...

351
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:31,670
...elf number one.

352
00:20:44,870 --> 00:20:47,550
- Did you bring the deep-dreamin' stuff?
- Got it.

353
00:20:47,630 --> 00:20:52,030
It's important they sleep and dream
they're on a wonderful flight to Canada.

354
00:20:52,110 --> 00:20:53,990
- I'm with the programme.
- Good.

355
00:20:54,070 --> 00:20:55,990
I may be sleepy, but I'm not stupid.

356
00:20:56,870 --> 00:20:58,630
Yeah, well, take the hat off.

357
00:20:58,710 --> 00:21:00,830
I get sniffly without my cap.

358
00:21:00,910 --> 00:21:02,870
OK, OK.

359
00:21:02,950 --> 00:21:04,310
All right, all right.

360
00:21:04,390 --> 00:21:06,710
Hey, Dad?

361
00:21:06,790 --> 00:21:09,670
Scott Calvin, as I live and breathe.

362
00:21:09,750 --> 00:21:11,590
Good thing you called.

363
00:21:11,670 --> 00:21:14,870
Otherwise I don't know
if I would've remembered you.

364
00:21:14,950 --> 00:21:16,870
It's me, good old Scott Calvin.

365
00:21:16,950 --> 00:21:18,990
You look a little like Father Time.

366
00:21:19,070 --> 00:21:21,430
Doesn't look anything
like Father Time.

367
00:21:25,790 --> 00:21:28,430
Oh. That's a nice door.

368
00:21:28,509 --> 00:21:30,950
Well, thank you. Yeah.
It was a little sticky,

369
00:21:31,030 --> 00:21:32,550
but smooth as a baby's butt now.

370
00:21:32,629 --> 00:21:35,070
- Come, take a feel.
- Oh, why not, huh?

371
00:21:35,190 --> 00:21:36,590
Look at that.

372
00:21:36,670 --> 00:21:38,950
Very butt-like.

373
00:21:39,030 --> 00:21:40,230
Who's your pal?

374
00:21:40,350 --> 00:21:43,790
Sandy. This is my associate.
He'll be taking us to the airport.

375
00:21:43,910 --> 00:21:47,350
- An associate? Business must be good.
- Busy as usual.

376
00:21:47,470 --> 00:21:51,150
So busy you can't bring our daughter
to visit her mother and father?

377
00:21:51,230 --> 00:21:52,710
Scott.

378
00:21:52,830 --> 00:21:55,710
Oh, so nice to see you.

379
00:21:55,830 --> 00:21:57,830
- You too, Sylvia.
- And your friend?

380
00:21:57,950 --> 00:22:00,070
- Sandy.
- Sandy.

381
00:22:00,189 --> 00:22:01,870
Nice to meet you.

382
00:22:01,990 --> 00:22:05,470
Do you know how excited
we were to get your phone call?

383
00:22:05,590 --> 00:22:08,950
See, we get so few,
and each one is special.

384
00:22:09,070 --> 00:22:10,310
Oh, come on, you guys,

385
00:22:10,390 --> 00:22:12,230
you'll catch pneumonia out here.

386
00:22:13,270 --> 00:22:15,750
It's so wonderful
to have you all here.

387
00:22:15,829 --> 00:22:17,230
- Festive.
- Easy.

388
00:22:17,310 --> 00:22:18,910
Please, please sit down.

389
00:22:18,989 --> 00:22:21,790
Oh, no, no, no. No.
We gotta get to the airport.

390
00:22:21,869 --> 00:22:24,990
Kind of a hurry. Let's get
your bags and pop 'em in the car.

391
00:22:25,070 --> 00:22:26,750
- I'm almost packed.
- Great!

392
00:22:26,830 --> 00:22:31,869
Throw my underwear in a bag. It's not
like we're going to the North Pole.

393
00:22:31,950 --> 00:22:33,670
- It's cold in Canada.
- Well...

394
00:22:33,750 --> 00:22:35,590
Remember when we went to Yosemite?

395
00:22:35,670 --> 00:22:37,349
Oh, here we go, Yosemite again.

396
00:22:37,430 --> 00:22:39,870
It was freezing
and there were bears.

397
00:22:39,949 --> 00:22:41,630
You never left the lodge.

398
00:22:41,710 --> 00:22:43,910
Because it was freezing.

399
00:22:43,990 --> 00:22:46,750
- And there were bears?
- Yes! And it was freezing.

400
00:22:46,829 --> 00:22:50,150
- It was freezing weather?
- It was in the freezing weather.

401
00:22:50,230 --> 00:22:53,430
Let me understand.
You did not enjoy the trip to Yosemite?

402
00:22:53,510 --> 00:22:55,270
- You heard me.
- I heard you.

403
00:23:10,350 --> 00:23:11,350
What?

404
00:23:11,430 --> 00:23:13,470
What part of our plan was not clear?

405
00:23:13,549 --> 00:23:16,390
Let's put them to sleep
when they get into the car.

406
00:23:16,470 --> 00:23:19,469
I couldn't stand to hear
the Yosemite story anymore.

407
00:23:19,550 --> 00:23:22,710
OK. So let's figure how we'll
get in the car. We'll both...

408
00:23:22,790 --> 00:23:24,470
Sandman, what are you doing?

409
00:23:27,510 --> 00:23:30,029
What? Sandman. Sandman!

410
00:23:32,150 --> 00:23:35,509
Great, I get to throw
his underwear in a bag.

411
00:23:59,509 --> 00:24:02,310
Hey, Mrs C. What you doing?

412
00:24:02,430 --> 00:24:04,230
Oh, hi, Jack.

413
00:24:04,350 --> 00:24:07,069
I'm trying to pick a tree
the whole family will love.

414
00:24:07,150 --> 00:24:09,509
Ah, family.

415
00:24:09,630 --> 00:24:12,910
You know, I cannot imagine
how hard it must be

416
00:24:12,990 --> 00:24:15,549
keeping such a big secret
from your folks.

417
00:24:15,630 --> 00:24:18,070
Oh, you have no idea.

418
00:24:20,310 --> 00:24:22,149
Tell me, Mrs Claus...

419
00:24:22,230 --> 00:24:24,309
...being legendary by marriage,

420
00:24:24,390 --> 00:24:27,790
do you ever find yourself wondering
if it's all really worth it?

421
00:24:29,710 --> 00:24:31,910
Well, it's definitely worth it.

422
00:24:33,990 --> 00:24:37,710
I'm sure dropping your life,
schlepping all the way to the North Pole

423
00:24:37,789 --> 00:24:39,949
- has been totally worthwhile.
- Yeah.

424
00:24:40,030 --> 00:24:43,150
Probably not one iota,
not even a scintilla, of regret?

425
00:24:43,229 --> 00:24:44,830
- Not one.
- Yeah.

426
00:24:44,909 --> 00:24:48,950
Look at that. Oh, dear.
A little sad, neglected maybe.

427
00:24:49,029 --> 00:24:51,069
Just needs a little tender loving care

428
00:24:51,150 --> 00:24:54,470
that nobody's bothering to give,
don't you think?

429
00:24:57,669 --> 00:24:59,429
It's perfect.

430
00:24:59,510 --> 00:25:02,349
I will give you all
the TLC that you need.

431
00:25:02,429 --> 00:25:04,389
Scott loves decorating the tree.

432
00:25:04,470 --> 00:25:07,990
He always insists on putting
the tree topper on himself.

433
00:25:09,429 --> 00:25:10,470
Ho ho ho!

434
00:25:12,749 --> 00:25:14,350
They're here!

435
00:25:15,430 --> 00:25:17,429
This is so exciting.

436
00:25:40,910 --> 00:25:43,629
I'm here! I cannot believe it!
I'm actually here!

437
00:25:43,709 --> 00:25:47,070
What a wonderful surprise.
I didn't know you were coming.

438
00:25:47,189 --> 00:25:49,469
- Uncle Scott brought me.
- Hey.

439
00:25:49,590 --> 00:25:51,230
And we tagged along!

440
00:25:51,350 --> 00:25:53,790
Hey! Hey! Hi!

441
00:25:53,909 --> 00:25:56,629
Oh, it's tall people...
Not that you're not tall.

442
00:25:56,710 --> 00:25:57,910
Surprise!

443
00:25:58,029 --> 00:26:00,670
- Hello!
- Oh, you look wonderful.

444
00:26:00,749 --> 00:26:02,909
- Really?
- You are glowing.

445
00:26:03,030 --> 00:26:06,389
- What did you think of my parents?
- They slept the entire trip.

446
00:26:06,509 --> 00:26:09,069
This is amazing!
Can we see the workshop?

447
00:26:09,149 --> 00:26:10,749
Yes. Go right there.
Go ahead.

448
00:26:10,830 --> 00:26:12,149
Oh, wait, wait, wait!

449
00:26:12,229 --> 00:26:16,190
My mom and dad can't know we're
at Santa's workshop in the North Pole.

450
00:26:16,269 --> 00:26:17,670
Where do they think we are?

451
00:26:17,749 --> 00:26:19,149
Welcome to Canada!

452
00:26:20,629 --> 00:26:22,109
Eh?

453
00:26:23,469 --> 00:26:25,869
An easy flight,
we cruised through customs.

454
00:26:25,949 --> 00:26:28,670
Oh, what a strange flight.

455
00:26:28,749 --> 00:26:30,870
Go, go, go.

456
00:26:30,949 --> 00:26:32,949
It was like a dream.

457
00:26:34,749 --> 00:26:37,030
And such a nice meal.

458
00:26:37,109 --> 00:26:38,550
They gave you a meal?

459
00:26:38,629 --> 00:26:40,669
I got four nuts in a pouch.

460
00:26:40,749 --> 00:26:42,869
And you had us sit in coach.

461
00:26:42,949 --> 00:26:45,510
No, that was first class.

462
00:26:45,589 --> 00:26:48,309
And I got a chance to sit
next to Tony Bennett.

463
00:26:48,390 --> 00:26:49,749
Mom! Dad!

464
00:26:49,829 --> 00:26:52,510
Sweetheart! Sweetheart.

465
00:26:52,589 --> 00:26:54,430
- Come here.
- Oh, you!

466
00:26:54,509 --> 00:26:55,869
Look at you, look at you.

467
00:26:55,950 --> 00:26:57,909
And look at this, look at this.

468
00:26:57,990 --> 00:26:59,189
It could be twins.

469
00:26:59,269 --> 00:27:03,109
But since you married the toymaker,
we don't get a lot of information.

470
00:27:03,189 --> 00:27:05,229
Oh, honey, just stop it, OK?

471
00:27:05,309 --> 00:27:09,149
Sweetheart, I am just so happy
to see you, darling.

472
00:27:09,230 --> 00:27:11,710
I'm so happy to see you, too, Mom.

473
00:27:11,789 --> 00:27:13,949
I'm sure you have
a perfectly good reason

474
00:27:14,030 --> 00:27:16,069
for shutting us out of your life.

475
00:27:28,789 --> 00:27:31,309
Magnificent.

476
00:27:31,389 --> 00:27:33,069
It's amazing.

477
00:27:33,149 --> 00:27:34,869
Killer.

478
00:27:40,390 --> 00:27:42,829
Please remember,
you're welcome to observe,

479
00:27:42,909 --> 00:27:45,509
but don't touch
or interfere with toy-making.

480
00:27:45,590 --> 00:27:48,029
I'll make sure she
doesn't get into anything.

481
00:27:48,109 --> 00:27:50,469
Look! Kobi the Magic Panda
and accessories!

482
00:27:50,589 --> 00:27:51,869
Lucy!

483
00:27:51,949 --> 00:27:53,989
Lucy, come back here.
Whoa!

484
00:27:54,069 --> 00:27:55,629
Trains.

485
00:27:55,709 --> 00:27:58,350
I'm... I'm just gonna go make a doll!

486
00:28:04,029 --> 00:28:06,030
Oh, excellent job.

487
00:28:06,149 --> 00:28:08,309
Bang, bang!

488
00:28:15,989 --> 00:28:17,229
Isn't that fun?

489
00:28:17,309 --> 00:28:18,989
Faster, worker elves, faster.

490
00:28:25,230 --> 00:28:28,110
The Hall of Snow Globes, perhaps?

491
00:28:40,590 --> 00:28:43,389
What might we have here.

492
00:28:46,109 --> 00:28:48,509
It's a lot of beans.

493
