740
00:43:50,668 --> 00:43:53,388
It's my very favourite,
just like you gave Charlie.

741
00:43:53,467 --> 00:43:55,348
Yeah. You know,

742
00:43:55,468 --> 00:43:57,587
I'm kind of partial to this one myself.

743
00:43:57,707 --> 00:43:59,107
Look, it's snowin'.

744
00:44:02,107 --> 00:44:04,587
Yeah. You got a good collection.

745
00:44:04,707 --> 00:44:07,067
Too bad you don't have one like this.

746
00:44:08,467 --> 00:44:11,628
- It's... It's me.
- Yeah.

747
00:44:14,027 --> 00:44:15,947
Hugging a snowman.

748
00:44:19,068 --> 00:44:21,548
Oh! And he turns pink!

749
00:44:21,627 --> 00:44:24,747
I told you your warm hugs were magical.

750
00:44:24,828 --> 00:44:27,028
Thank you for my present, Santa.

751
00:44:27,107 --> 00:44:29,508
It's OK.

752
00:44:30,588 --> 00:44:32,228
Well, look at it this way.

753
00:44:32,307 --> 00:44:35,108
One down, 2.6 billion to go.

754
00:44:35,187 --> 00:44:37,708
We better get out of here.

755
00:44:37,787 --> 00:44:39,387
Hold on, here we go.

756
00:45:19,987 --> 00:45:22,507
Do you want me
to put on the tree topper?

757
00:45:22,587 --> 00:45:25,308
Save it for Scott.
He always puts the tree topper on.

758
00:45:25,387 --> 00:45:27,747
Of course.

759
00:45:29,587 --> 00:45:32,148
It's strange how much

760
00:45:32,227 --> 00:45:34,467
this resembles...

761
00:45:38,827 --> 00:45:41,628
- Hi, honey, I'm back.
- Oh, honey, are you OK?

762
00:45:41,707 --> 00:45:44,667
Great. Good news is
I get to spend time with you guys.

763
00:45:44,747 --> 00:45:46,548
Scott.

764
00:45:46,627 --> 00:45:48,068
Sir.

765
00:45:48,147 --> 00:45:49,588
Sorry to interrupt.

766
00:45:52,107 --> 00:45:54,388
There's something
you need to check twice.

767
00:45:57,108 --> 00:45:58,068
Two minutes?

768
00:46:02,068 --> 00:46:05,027
What? What?

769
00:46:06,227 --> 00:46:11,467
We have a problem. This is unreadable.
Because it's all crinkled up.

770
00:46:11,587 --> 00:46:14,388
You gotta plan it out.
It's gotta be in my office.

771
00:46:14,507 --> 00:46:16,507
Yeah, my office.

772
00:46:16,588 --> 00:46:18,467
- Neil?
- What?

773
00:46:18,547 --> 00:46:21,427
Let's go find Lucy,
get her washed up for dinner, OK?

774
00:46:21,507 --> 00:46:23,308
Leave that here.
Leave it.

775
00:46:24,268 --> 00:46:25,427
We'll be right back.

776
00:46:30,547 --> 00:46:31,948
Don't worry, honey.

777
00:46:33,067 --> 00:46:34,347
That's not gonna work.

778
00:46:34,428 --> 00:46:36,387
It's busy season.

779
00:46:36,467 --> 00:46:38,747
It's always his busy season.

780
00:46:48,907 --> 00:46:52,587
That's Uncle Scott's snow globe.
You're not supposed to have that.

781
00:46:52,668 --> 00:46:56,067
- I know. Isn't it great?
- It's not great at all.

782
00:46:56,147 --> 00:46:59,867
You've done a terrible thing.
You'll be on the naughty list for life.

783
00:46:59,947 --> 00:47:02,227
But naughty list people have more fun.

784
00:47:02,307 --> 00:47:05,747
- I'm going for help.
- I wouldn't do that.

785
00:47:07,147 --> 00:47:09,787
Mom, Dad! Over here, quick!

786
00:47:09,867 --> 00:47:11,147
- Lucy!
- What?

787
00:47:12,787 --> 00:47:14,707
- Come on, hurry!
- What's wrong?

788
00:47:16,787 --> 00:47:17,787
What's wrong?

789
00:47:18,747 --> 00:47:20,427
Sweetheart, what is it?

790
00:47:21,387 --> 00:47:23,707
I told you not to do that.

791
00:47:23,787 --> 00:47:27,747
Jack Frost took Uncle Scott's snow globe
and he knows that it's not his.

792
00:47:31,547 --> 00:47:32,627
Stop!

793
00:47:34,707 --> 00:47:35,867
Stop!

794
00:47:37,667 --> 00:47:40,667
Don't! What did you do?

795
00:47:40,747 --> 00:47:42,347
I froze them.

796
00:47:45,347 --> 00:47:48,627
Now, am I gonna have to do
the same thing to you?

797
00:47:48,747 --> 00:47:53,867
Or are you going to get in that closet
and stay there without saying a word?

798
00:48:02,147 --> 00:48:03,387
Smart girl.

799
00:48:06,027 --> 00:48:08,827
Oh, smile, will you?

800
00:48:08,947 --> 00:48:12,107
I've had kids beg me
to freeze their parents.

801
00:48:14,107 --> 00:48:17,707
And to think I asked you to be my elf.

802
00:48:19,307 --> 00:48:21,987
Of course all those bears
are machine-washable.

803
00:48:22,067 --> 00:48:25,307
Right. Just put it on the card.
I can't be in two places at once.

804
00:48:25,387 --> 00:48:29,107
You gotta manage and stop
calling every time something goes wrong.

805
00:48:29,187 --> 00:48:31,467
I'm a little busy
with my family, Curtis.

806
00:48:31,547 --> 00:48:34,667
All I want to see is
busy, busy worker tushies.

807
00:48:34,747 --> 00:48:36,587
Hey, hey,
I'm rolling downhill.

808
00:48:36,667 --> 00:48:38,627
This is not up to code,
this building.

809
00:48:38,707 --> 00:48:40,427
You're number one. Act like it.

810
00:48:40,507 --> 00:48:42,747
Why haven't you put
the tree topper on yet?

811
00:48:42,827 --> 00:48:44,706
Scott's just been a little busy.

812
00:48:47,306 --> 00:48:49,226
Tell your dad to do it.

813
00:48:49,307 --> 00:48:53,187
And then watch the suddenly displaced
Mr Claus run right over.

814
00:48:53,267 --> 00:48:54,787
Go ahead. It'll be fun.

815
00:48:54,867 --> 00:48:57,307
Dad, do you wanna help me
with the tree topper?

816
00:48:57,387 --> 00:48:58,867
Yeah, in a minute.

817
00:49:01,947 --> 00:49:03,787
I don't know who he is anymore.

818
00:49:03,867 --> 00:49:05,707
I don't know who he is, either.

819
00:49:05,787 --> 00:49:08,307
Neil, Lucy and Laura
should be here for this.

820
00:49:08,387 --> 00:49:10,307
They left a while ago.

821
00:49:10,387 --> 00:49:12,747
Some Canadians invited them
over for cocoa.

822
00:49:12,826 --> 00:49:15,627
You know how they are.
Yak-yak, yak-yak, eh?

823
00:49:16,587 --> 00:49:19,987
Scott? Tree topper, what do you say?

824
00:49:20,067 --> 00:49:22,907
Scott, honey,
let's put the tree topper on.

825
00:49:22,987 --> 00:49:26,386
- We can make a toast.
- You built this place on a fault line.

826
00:49:26,467 --> 00:49:30,106
Millions of kids in Australia go
without gifts. What can I do for you?

827
00:49:30,187 --> 00:49:33,307
- Tree topper.
- Oh, yeah, tree topper. Good.

828
00:49:33,386 --> 00:49:34,587
Scott? Toast.

829
00:49:36,107 --> 00:49:37,187
Just a second.

830
00:49:39,067 --> 00:49:40,587
Good.

831
00:49:40,666 --> 00:49:43,907
Bad. Well, good for goodness sakes.

832
00:49:43,987 --> 00:49:47,147
Yeah. Uh-huh.
Curtis, I can't talk right now,

833
00:49:47,227 --> 00:49:50,427
I'm putting the tree topper on.
It's important. Can't talk.

834
00:49:50,546 --> 00:49:52,427
Curtis, please, please, I gotta go.

835
00:49:52,547 --> 00:49:53,667
Bye.

836
00:49:57,067 --> 00:49:59,787
Gonna put it in my pocket.
I'm not answering that.

837
00:49:59,907 --> 00:50:03,347
I'm putting the phone in my pocket.
Put it in my pocket. All done.

838
00:50:03,426 --> 00:50:07,187
OK, everybody, as I climb up
this beautiful tree,

839
00:50:07,307 --> 00:50:09,707
I know we've had our ups and downs.

840
00:50:09,827 --> 00:50:12,066
But as I place this tree topper

841
00:50:12,186 --> 00:50:13,787
in the traditional place,

842
00:50:13,907 --> 00:50:15,787
I just want to say...

843
00:50:38,907 --> 00:50:40,746
Be careful, honey.

844
00:51:00,186 --> 00:51:02,467
Oh, honey.

845
00:51:03,667 --> 00:51:06,587
Honey... I think maybe I can fix that.

846
00:51:07,987 --> 00:51:09,187
I know you're upset.

847
00:51:09,266 --> 00:51:11,107
You picked up on that, did you?

848
00:51:11,186 --> 00:51:14,586
Bud, what is that supposed to mean?

849
00:51:14,667 --> 00:51:17,147
If you weren't working
all the time you'd know.

850
00:51:17,226 --> 00:51:19,666
You don't understand
the pressure I'm under.

851
00:51:19,747 --> 00:51:23,187
Well, maybe it's not as bad
as being ripped away from your family

852
00:51:23,266 --> 00:51:25,586
- and told you can't see them anymore.
- Dad.

853
00:51:25,667 --> 00:51:28,387
Maybe I invited you here
so Carol can be surrounded

854
00:51:28,466 --> 00:51:32,227
by family for love and support while
I do things you can't even imagine.

855
00:51:32,306 --> 00:51:35,347
Rather than make things work,
you make things worse.

856
00:51:35,426 --> 00:51:36,706
We're leaving.

857
00:51:36,787 --> 00:51:39,747
- What?
- Maybe we shouldn't have come.

858
00:51:41,707 --> 00:51:44,226
Maybe you're right.
You shouldn't have come.

859
00:51:45,427 --> 00:51:48,107
Maybe I should never have come either.

860
00:51:48,186 --> 00:51:50,627
Don't say anything you'll regret.

861
00:51:51,827 --> 00:51:54,867
I think we all need
to cool down for a second.

862
00:51:58,106 --> 00:51:59,907
Why don't you and I take a walk?

863
00:52:00,026 --> 00:52:01,827
Let's go. Let's just go.

864
00:52:06,067 --> 00:52:07,867
Oh, sweetheart.

865
00:52:34,747 --> 00:52:36,307
It's over.

866
00:52:36,387 --> 00:52:41,787
I thought I had a second chance
at having a family, but I blew it again.

867
00:52:42,626 --> 00:52:46,267
Hey. There's no one I know who could
hold this all together but you.

868
00:52:46,346 --> 00:52:47,627
But I didn't.

869
00:52:48,747 --> 00:52:51,826
My in-laws resent me,
Christmas is a disaster,

870
00:52:51,907 --> 00:52:54,706
and my pregnant wife wishes
that she never had met me.

871
00:52:56,106 --> 00:52:58,866
I was gonna wait until tomorrow
to give you this,

872
00:52:58,946 --> 00:53:00,387
but...

873
00:53:00,466 --> 00:53:03,746
I think you need
a bit of a pick-me-up now.

874
00:53:03,827 --> 00:53:05,787
- I can't.
- Come on. Open it.

875
00:53:05,866 --> 00:53:08,706
- I don't feel like it.
- It'll make you feel better.

876
00:53:08,787 --> 00:53:13,027
- I don't feel like it.
- Come on, open it, please.

877
00:53:13,106 --> 00:53:14,906
Thanks.

878
00:53:17,106 --> 00:53:19,587
So are there times when you wonder...

879
00:53:21,706 --> 00:53:22,907
Wonder what?

880
00:53:22,986 --> 00:53:25,627
- If this was even...
- Worth it?

881
00:53:25,706 --> 00:53:28,706
More than you know.

882
00:53:30,386 --> 00:53:32,426
Tonight's one of these times, huh?

883
00:53:32,507 --> 00:53:34,707
Wish I'd never put that red coat on.

884
00:53:34,786 --> 00:53:38,267
So... you wish you'd
never become Santa at all?

885
00:53:38,346 --> 00:53:41,226
I wish I'd never become Santa.

886
00:53:42,186 --> 00:53:43,347
At all?

887
00:53:45,107 --> 00:53:47,467
At all. At all.

888
00:53:47,546 --> 00:53:49,426
Yeah, at all.

889
00:53:50,666 --> 00:53:53,706
I wished I'd never been
Santa at all. Happy?

890
00:53:55,226 --> 00:53:56,706
I am now.

891
00:54:00,106 --> 00:54:01,987
No!

892
00:54:18,106 --> 00:54:19,947
Ho ho ho.

893
00:54:25,386 --> 00:54:26,586
Hey, you!

894
00:54:26,667 --> 00:54:28,946
Ho ho... Uh-oh!

895
00:54:40,186 --> 00:54:41,986
Get off me, blubber ball!

896
00:54:42,066 --> 00:54:43,947
I will not let you put on that coat!

897
00:54:44,026 --> 00:54:45,266
Oh, yeah? Watch me!

898
00:54:45,346 --> 00:54:47,346
Don't even think about it, Jack.

899
00:54:57,426 --> 00:54:59,906
You hit me with a shovel!

900
00:55:03,506 --> 00:55:05,347
Adios, fatty!

901
00:55:06,186 --> 00:55:08,426
No, Frost, no!

902
00:55:10,026 --> 00:55:11,986
Oh, no.

903
00:55:28,626 --> 00:55:31,146
OK, so, the Mississippi
factory needs to know

904
00:55:31,226 --> 00:55:34,786
if we want them to ship
100,000 units or 200,000.

905
00:55:34,866 --> 00:55:37,587
They won't ship tomorrow
because it's Christmas,

906
00:55:37,666 --> 00:55:40,546
but they will ship Thursday,
which means...

907
00:55:40,626 --> 00:55:43,506
- They're not gonna ship tomorrow?
- Yes, sir.

908
00:55:43,586 --> 00:55:46,666
- This is Christmas Eve?
- Yes, sir.

909
00:55:47,587 --> 00:55:49,626
What are you doing?
Why are we working?

910
00:55:49,706 --> 00:55:51,346
We always work Christmas Eve.

911
00:55:52,506 --> 00:55:54,026
- We do?
- Of course.

912
00:55:54,106 --> 00:55:56,306
Well, that... that's ridiculous.

913
00:55:56,426 --> 00:55:59,466
Christmas Eve is when you
spend time with your family.

914
00:55:59,546 --> 00:56:03,907
- Where's my family tonight?
- I really don't know, Mr Calvin.

915
00:56:03,986 --> 00:56:05,466
What do you mean?

916
00:56:05,586 --> 00:56:06,906
Well, you rarely see them

917
00:56:07,026 --> 00:56:10,506
and you... don't mention them.

918
00:56:12,786 --> 00:56:14,186
Where are my car keys?

919
00:56:24,466 --> 00:56:25,906
Hey.

920
00:56:25,986 --> 00:56:27,986
What are you doing here?

921
00:56:28,066 --> 00:56:30,546
Well, I just came over to see...

922
00:56:30,626 --> 00:56:35,226
See what? Why on earth would you
drag yourself all the way over here?

923
00:56:35,306 --> 00:56:37,626
- Is that Derek?
- No.

924
00:56:37,706 --> 00:56:40,426
- And you're not going out tonight.
- Yeah, OK.

925
00:56:40,906 --> 00:56:44,266
- What are you doing here?
- Came over to see you.

926
00:56:45,226 --> 00:56:46,306
Why?

927
00:56:47,866 --> 00:56:49,986
Cause we don't see
each other enough.

928
00:56:51,506 --> 00:56:53,506
- What?
- Come on, Charlie.

929
00:56:53,586 --> 00:56:54,786
I'm outta here.

930
00:56:54,866 --> 00:56:58,306
- Charlie, it's Christmas Eve.
- Like either of us care, Mom?

931
00:56:58,386 --> 00:56:59,906
- Charlie.
- What?

932
00:56:59,986 --> 00:57:01,826
Come back here. Charlie!

933
00:57:01,906 --> 00:57:04,346
- Good night, Scott.
- Wait, wait!

934
00:57:05,426 --> 00:57:07,746
Can you help me find Carol?

935
00:57:07,826 --> 00:57:09,666
- Carol?
- Carol Newman.

936
00:57:10,826 --> 00:57:13,586
Carol Newman, the principal
of Charlie's school?

937
00:57:13,666 --> 00:57:17,306
- Yeah. Do you know where she is?
- I don't know. She moved away.

938
00:57:17,386 --> 00:57:20,626
Ran out of local kids to terrify,
I guess. I don't know.

939
00:57:20,706 --> 00:57:22,266
What is the matter with you?

940
00:57:22,346 --> 00:57:25,226
Neil. Neil and Lucy,
they'll understand.

941
00:57:25,306 --> 00:57:28,506
- Where are they?
- At the North Pole.

942
00:57:28,586 --> 00:57:29,946
At the North Pole?

943
00:57:34,145 --> 00:57:36,786
Yeah. The North Pole.

944
00:57:37,386 --> 00:57:39,706
- Frost.
- What?

945
00:57:39,786 --> 00:57:42,466
Frost turned the North Pole
into a theme park.

946
00:57:43,546 --> 00:57:45,866
Neil has been taking Lucy
to the North Pole

947
00:57:45,945 --> 00:57:48,106
ever since he and I got our divorce.

948
00:57:49,666 --> 00:57:50,986
Divorce?

949
00:57:52,906 --> 00:57:54,946
Are you sure you should be driving?

950
00:57:56,186 --> 00:57:59,546
I'm gonna make everything OK.
I'll make everything better.

951
00:58:01,066 --> 00:58:02,866
Yeah. OK.

952
00:59:09,026 --> 00:59:10,866
Get a ticket. We were here first.

953
00:59:13,346 --> 00:59:14,866
I hate it. I'm not getting on.

954
00:59:14,945 --> 00:59:17,786
- I'm not made of money, all right?
- Let's go.

955
00:59:17,866 --> 00:59:21,586
<i>Try our gingerbread houses.
They're Santalicious.

956
00:59:24,226 --> 00:59:26,786
<i>Don't forget to buy
a ticket for Santa's show.

957
00:59:28,066 --> 00:59:30,305
Do I look like
a cash machine to you?

958
00:59:30,386 --> 00:59:32,625
I want a dancing Santa!

959
00:59:36,106 --> 00:59:37,666
Keep moving. Come on.

960
00:59:37,746 --> 00:59:40,065
Forget it, that's it.

961
00:59:41,226 --> 00:59:43,026
- I saw it first.
- No, you didn't.

962
00:59:43,106 --> 00:59:44,705
- I'm buying it.
- Give it to me!

963
00:59:44,786 --> 00:59:46,586
- No way!
- Mom!

964
00:59:49,306 --> 00:59:51,985
- Dad, I don't like this.
- That's just too bad.

965
00:59:53,266 --> 00:59:54,826
Hey, stand somewhere else.

966
00:59:56,385 --> 00:59:58,746
You stay right here with me
and hold my hand!

967
01:00:01,906 --> 01:00:05,506
- I wanna see reindeer.
- Stop pushing!

968
01:00:06,626 --> 01:00:09,626
- Why are we here?
- Because you wanted to...

969
01:00:09,746 --> 01:00:11,786
<i>Kids, how much your parents love you

970
01:00:11,906 --> 01:00:14,546
<i>depends on how much
they spend on your present.

971
01:00:14,666 --> 01:00:16,746
Hurry up, Dad, let's go!

972
01:00:18,025 --> 01:00:20,466
- Come on, I want a ride!
- Lucy!

973
01:00:20,586 --> 01:00:23,706
- Neil!
- Scott Calvin.

974
01:00:23,785 --> 01:00:25,465
Odd place to run into you.

975
01:00:27,826 --> 01:00:29,186
Luce?

976
01:00:29,265 --> 01:00:31,465
What's up, Mr Calvin?

977
01:00:31,546 --> 01:00:33,265
Can we please go?

978
01:00:34,065 --> 01:00:37,385
Wait, wait, wait. What happened
between you and Laura?

979
01:00:37,466 --> 01:00:41,386
I know you think therapy is like
witchcraft, but you might consider it.

980
01:00:41,465 --> 01:00:44,306
Please, please, just tell me.

981
01:00:46,746 --> 01:00:49,626
You don't really know
because you were never around.

982
01:00:49,705 --> 01:00:51,745
It shouldn't be any news to you, Scott.

983
01:00:51,826 --> 01:00:53,746
You were never a father to Charlie.

984
01:00:53,825 --> 01:00:56,626
You put all the pressure on me,
and guess what?

985
01:00:56,705 --> 01:00:58,706
He didn't want me to be his father...

986
01:01:00,786 --> 01:01:04,105
...which messed things up pretty good
between me and Laura.

987
01:01:04,186 --> 01:01:05,905
Want me to go on, Scott?

988
01:01:05,986 --> 01:01:08,665
Come on, Dad, the line's getting longer.

989
01:01:13,666 --> 01:01:15,026
Excuse me, sir.

990
01:01:16,305 --> 01:01:17,626
- Curtis.
- Yes, sir.

991
01:01:17,705 --> 01:01:21,385
Can I offer you two tickets for a turn
to build a toy with Santa's elves?

992
01:01:21,466 --> 01:01:26,185
I'll throw in this commemorative pen,
voice-enhanced. Cash or credit card?

993
01:01:26,266 --> 01:01:28,346
<i>- Cash or credit card?
- That's silly.

994
01:01:28,426 --> 01:01:31,145
Not sure, I'll throw in
a pass for the nice list.

995
01:01:31,226 --> 01:01:32,625
Walk with me, won't you?

996
01:01:32,706 --> 01:01:35,346
Curtis, it's me.
Oh, for the love of candy canes,

997
01:01:35,426 --> 01:01:36,946
what have you done here?

998
01:01:37,025 --> 01:01:41,305
Well, sir, this is a nice list kiosk.
The line ends by the petting zoo.

999
01:01:41,385 --> 01:01:44,305
Parents pay to have
their kids put on the nice list?

1000
01:01:44,386 --> 01:01:47,465
Not right. I better change things
back the way they were.

1001
01:01:47,546 --> 01:01:49,385
Who's your boss?

1002
01:01:49,466 --> 01:01:51,025
Where's Frost?

1003
01:01:51,825 --> 01:01:53,345
Curtis, where's Frost?

1004
01:01:53,426 --> 01:01:56,105
- Security!
- Bring Frost out here right now!

1005
01:01:56,186 --> 01:01:58,066
I'll take care of him.

1006
01:02:01,346 --> 01:02:02,906
Look, there's Santa.

1007
01:02:04,146 --> 01:02:07,106
<i>Nice to see you, mon frere.
I've been waiting.

1008
01:02:07,225 --> 01:02:09,346
Has it been 12 years already?

1009
01:02:09,466 --> 01:02:12,705
Frost. What have you done?

1010
01:02:12,825 --> 01:02:14,465
Hey. Easy does it, Armani man.

1011
01:02:14,585 --> 01:02:17,065
No hello? Love what you've
done with the place?

1012
01:02:17,185 --> 01:02:19,265
<i>Shave a reindeer for five dollars.

1013
01:02:19,385 --> 01:02:23,186
What about the secret of Santa?
How could you do this to the North Pole?

1014
01:02:23,265 --> 01:02:26,186
The whole thing is way too much work,
too much pressure.

1015
01:02:26,265 --> 01:02:28,546
No one even thanks you
for all the effort.

1016
01:02:28,625 --> 01:02:31,785
No thank yous? What about
the plates of cookies and milk?

1017
01:02:31,865 --> 01:02:33,866
Please, I'm cleansing.

1018
01:02:33,945 --> 01:02:36,186
I stopped the whole
toy delivery nonsense

1019
01:02:36,265 --> 01:02:38,946
and brought anyone
who could afford to pay up here.

1020
01:02:39,745 --> 01:02:43,265
Who needs magic? Who needs to be
crawling on roofs and chimneys?

1021
01:02:43,346 --> 01:02:45,826
I got everything I need right here.

1022
01:02:45,905 --> 01:02:50,385
Look around. This isn't how the North
Pole's supposed to be. This is wrong.

1023
01:02:50,466 --> 01:02:52,946
Why don't you chill out
and enjoy the swag, huh?

1024
01:02:53,025 --> 01:02:55,305
This junk is not
what Christmas is about.

1025
01:02:55,386 --> 01:02:58,026
- You're the one who gave it up.
- You tricked me.

1026
01:02:58,105 --> 01:03:01,225
- Give me a break.
- I didn't know you had my snow globe.

1027
01:03:01,306 --> 01:03:04,466
Maybe not, but who said,
"I wish I'd never been Santa at all"?

1028
01:03:04,545 --> 01:03:05,546
What?

1029
01:03:05,625 --> 01:03:08,706
I said, "Who said
'I wish I'd never been Santa at all'?"

1030
01:03:08,785 --> 01:03:10,786
Rudolph? Rudolph's mama?

1031
01:03:10,865 --> 01:03:13,625
Frost, switch back with me.
Now's your chance.

1032
01:03:13,705 --> 01:03:16,106
And this is your chance
to enjoy the show.

1033
01:03:16,185 --> 01:03:17,506
- Security.
- Yes, sir.

1034
01:03:17,585 --> 01:03:19,666
Take my guest to his seat, won't you?

1035
01:03:20,465 --> 01:03:21,705
Thanks so much.

1036
01:03:21,785 --> 01:03:23,705
Come on, let's go.

1037
01:03:23,786 --> 01:03:26,666
<i>Tickets on sale now
for the 6:00 elf toss.

1038
01:03:35,545 --> 01:03:38,425
<i>Never too late to get tickets
to Santa's show.

1039
01:04:02,625 --> 01:04:03,945
Hey, Luce.

1040
01:04:05,945 --> 01:04:08,506
I know something really
wonderful about you.

1041
01:04:09,545 --> 01:04:12,185
- You love snow globes.
- Yeah.

1042
01:04:12,305 --> 01:04:15,105
Well, if that's true,
I've got a surprise for you.

1043
01:04:15,226 --> 01:04:16,705
Just up those stairs,

1044
01:04:16,825 --> 01:04:19,385
behind the vending machine
is a secret room

1045
01:04:19,465 --> 01:04:22,385
filled with snow globes
like you've never seen before.

1046
01:04:22,465 --> 01:04:27,026
Beautiful snow globes. There's
a secret code to get in that room.

1047
01:04:27,105 --> 01:04:28,386
What's the code?

1048
01:04:35,946 --> 01:04:37,665
You grab the one in the middle

1049
01:04:37,745 --> 01:04:39,585
and bring it back down to me.

1050
01:04:39,665 --> 01:04:41,465
I need your help.

1051
01:04:41,545 --> 01:04:44,785
But I don't want to go
up there all alone.

1052
01:04:46,185 --> 01:04:47,785
Lucy...

1053
01:04:48,905 --> 01:04:50,145
...trust me.

1054
01:04:50,225 --> 01:04:52,145
This is really important.

1055
01:05:00,505 --> 01:05:02,665
- OK.
- OK.

1056
01:05:02,745 --> 01:05:06,025
OK. I'll create a little diversion.

1057
01:05:07,305 --> 01:05:09,145
Boy, this show stinks.

1058
01:05:09,225 --> 01:05:10,705
Come on.

1059
01:05:10,785 --> 01:05:12,305
Hey, hold it!

1060
01:05:12,385 --> 01:05:15,345
- Coming through.
- You can't catch me. Come on, guys.

1061
01:05:15,425 --> 01:05:17,145
Can't catch an old dog like me?

1062
01:05:17,225 --> 01:05:18,945
Lucy? Lucy!

1063
01:05:24,585 --> 01:05:27,305
<i>Grab a seat, everybody.
The show's about to begin.

1064
01:07:37,945 --> 01:07:40,185
Thank you! Thank you!

1065
01:07:44,185 --> 01:07:47,785
I'm gonna kick the coal
out of whoever did that.

1066
01:07:49,785 --> 01:07:52,225
- You.
- You're not Santa Claus.

1067
01:07:52,345 --> 01:07:54,865
That is an impostor. I'm Santa Claus.

1068
01:07:54,945 --> 01:07:57,825
Guards! Guards, get him!

1069
01:07:59,265 --> 01:08:02,145
Bring it on! Who wants
some of this? Come here!

1070
01:08:03,024 --> 01:08:05,985
If you don't mind...

1071
01:08:06,065 --> 01:08:08,385
Where are you going?
Get down from there!

1072
01:08:08,504 --> 01:08:10,305
Guess if you guys want me,

1073
01:08:10,424 --> 01:08:12,505
you're gonna have to come up here

1074
01:08:12,624 --> 01:08:14,505
and get me!

1075
01:08:46,224 --> 01:08:47,945
Get this through your head.

1076
01:08:48,025 --> 01:08:50,425
You're not Santa anymore.

1077
01:08:50,505 --> 01:08:53,784
You're just a guy
who smells like a cookie.

1078
01:09:01,225 --> 01:09:03,425
Hey, how about a game of catch?

1079
01:09:03,504 --> 01:09:05,105
Lucy, toss it.

1080
01:09:20,504 --> 01:09:22,665
Nice try, compadre.

1081
01:09:22,745 --> 01:09:28,385
And lovely teamwork.
There's only one problem.

1082
01:09:28,464 --> 01:09:30,625
You're never gonna get me to say...

1083
01:09:30,705 --> 01:09:32,945
<i>I wish I'd never been Santa at all.

1084
01:09:34,104 --> 01:09:36,585
Now who said that? Rudolph?

1085
01:09:36,664 --> 01:09:38,825
Rudolph's mama?

1086
01:09:43,585 --> 01:09:48,145
No!

1087
01:09:57,784 --> 01:09:59,665
Ho ho ho.

1088
01:10:02,744 --> 01:10:04,384
I gotta get my coat back.

1089
01:10:09,344 --> 01:10:10,465
Come here.

1090
01:10:11,664 --> 01:10:13,785
- Boy, you are just...
- Hey!

1091
01:10:22,025 --> 01:10:24,264
- Whoa. Freaky.
- Hey, you!

1092
01:10:24,385 --> 01:10:26,584
Ho ho... Uh-oh!

1093
01:10:26,665 --> 01:10:28,264
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

1094
01:10:36,145 --> 01:10:37,984
Let me go! That coat belongs to me.

1095
01:10:38,065 --> 01:10:40,545
No, Frost, that coat belongs to him.

1096
01:10:41,505 --> 01:10:42,585
You got him!

1097
01:10:42,664 --> 01:10:44,304
This guy was huge.

1098
01:10:44,385 --> 01:10:46,945
- I'm Santa now.
- You don't look like Santa.

1099
01:10:47,024 --> 01:10:49,425
- You killed him.
- Did not.

1100
01:10:49,504 --> 01:10:53,784
- I want my coat.
- Dad, you gotta see this.

1101
01:10:53,865 --> 01:10:56,585
Charlie, Charlie!
Stay away from those things.

1102
01:10:56,664 --> 01:10:58,105
I want the coat!

1103
01:10:58,184 --> 01:11:01,864
'Cause you make such a good Santa?
Because all the elves love you?

1104
01:11:01,945 --> 01:11:04,224
Those people you
took money from love you?

1105
01:11:04,304 --> 01:11:08,704
Listen to me, listen to me. Being
Santa's not something you could take.

1106
01:11:08,785 --> 01:11:11,064
It's something that chooses you.

1107
01:11:11,145 --> 01:11:14,145
Well... how do I look?
Nice?

1108
01:11:14,224 --> 01:11:15,704
And you're too late.

1109
01:11:21,785 --> 01:11:24,665
No!

1110
01:11:34,624 --> 01:11:36,225
Carol.

1111
01:11:37,465 --> 01:11:38,744
Carol!

1112
01:11:40,224 --> 01:11:42,624
Well, that didn't work out
the way I'd hoped.

1113
01:11:42,704 --> 01:11:44,824
Carol.

1114
01:11:44,904 --> 01:11:48,344
Oh, Scott.
We've been looking everywhere for you.

1115
01:11:48,425 --> 01:11:49,624
Come here.

1116
01:11:49,704 --> 01:11:51,544
Oh, Mrs Claus, I've missed you.

1117
01:11:51,624 --> 01:11:55,504
- I missed you so much, so much.
- Wait, it's just been a few minutes.

1118
01:11:57,504 --> 01:11:59,945
- It's only been a few minutes?
- Yes.

1119
01:12:00,065 --> 01:12:04,185
Of course. It only takes a few minutes
to see the truth of an entire lifetime.

1120
01:12:04,305 --> 01:12:06,744
- I don't understand.
- A man goes in the world,

1121
01:12:06,824 --> 01:12:09,464
and expects his dreams
to come true, and then...

1122
01:12:09,545 --> 01:12:12,664
...the unexpected happens.
Pick up a coat and become Santa.

1123
01:12:12,784 --> 01:12:17,184
That's huge! A lot of pressure, taking
care of the children of the world,

1124
01:12:17,304 --> 01:12:20,144
and the elves and the SOS
and the North Pole,

1125
01:12:20,264 --> 01:12:24,505
but he loses sight of what's important:
The woman who falls in love with him...

1126
01:12:25,504 --> 01:12:29,104
...and gives him a baby.

1127
01:12:29,184 --> 01:12:32,144
- I love being Santa and I love you.
- I love you, too.

1128
01:12:32,224 --> 01:12:35,544
- Have you been drinking cocoa?
- No. I'm back.

1129
01:12:36,504 --> 01:12:39,264
- I've missed you very, very much.
- I missed you too.

1130
01:12:42,344 --> 01:12:43,744
Ohh.

1131
01:12:43,825 --> 01:12:45,704
Hey, you guys know what happened?

1132
01:12:45,784 --> 01:12:48,065
- No.
- We ticked each other off. That's it.

1133
01:12:48,144 --> 01:12:50,945
Like families all over
the world do on Christmas Eve

1134
01:12:51,024 --> 01:12:53,544
that love each other,
ticking each other off.

1135
01:12:53,624 --> 01:12:58,104
They don't have to be perfect to be good
families. We just have to be together.

1136
01:12:58,864 --> 01:13:01,105
I'm still so very sorry

1137
01:13:01,184 --> 01:13:04,024
that we added to all
this pressure that you're under.

1138
01:13:05,544 --> 01:13:07,904
I think that we should apologise.
Don't you?

1139
01:13:07,984 --> 01:13:11,784
No. It's good I'm tough on him.
I'm his father-in-law. It's my job.

1140
01:13:11,864 --> 01:13:15,064
As long as you promise to do it
every Christmas, it's fine.

1141
01:13:15,144 --> 01:13:17,224
We'll see about that.
I'm a busy guy.

1142
01:13:17,304 --> 01:13:19,944
And so am I. And I'd like
to show you guys what I do.

1143
01:13:20,025 --> 01:13:22,144
- The SOS.
- The SOS is about secrets,

1144
01:13:22,225 --> 01:13:26,065
secrets aren't for families. I'm tired
of keeping you from your family.

1145
01:13:26,144 --> 01:13:29,144
So if you guys would
follow me to my factory.

1146
01:13:48,464 --> 01:13:50,024
Elves?

1147
01:13:51,264 --> 01:13:53,625
Elves! Stop working for a minute.

1148
01:13:53,744 --> 01:13:56,624
I'd like you all to say
hello to the in-laws.

1149
01:13:56,704 --> 01:13:59,665
Hello, in-laws!

1150
01:13:59,744 --> 01:14:02,265
- Hello.
- How ya doin'?

1151
01:14:05,344 --> 01:14:06,984
- Elves.
- Oh, my.

1152
01:14:07,064 --> 01:14:09,344
They're not Canadians. They're elves.

1153
01:14:09,424 --> 01:14:10,904
Never said... in person...

1154
01:14:11,024 --> 01:14:12,984
Listen, if they're elves,

1155
01:14:13,064 --> 01:14:14,864
this is not a toy factory.

1156
01:14:14,984 --> 01:14:17,344
This is probably Santa's workshop.

1157
01:14:17,464 --> 01:14:20,864
- And if this is probably...
- If this is Santa's workshop,

1158
01:14:20,984 --> 01:14:23,024
...then... he...
- Then he's the guy.

1159
01:14:24,024 --> 01:14:27,304
Hey, you... you're the guy.
You're Father Christmas.

1160
01:14:27,384 --> 01:14:30,385
It's a little freaky,
but... you'll get used to it.

1161
01:14:31,384 --> 01:14:33,104
- Whoa!
- Oh!

1162
01:14:33,184 --> 01:14:34,424
Whoa!

1163
01:14:34,504 --> 01:14:37,304
If you're Father Christmas
that means

1164
01:14:37,384 --> 01:14:39,544
I'm Father Christmas' father-in-law.

1165
01:14:39,624 --> 01:14:43,584
That means I'm...
I'm Father-in-law Christmas.

1166
01:14:43,664 --> 01:14:46,224
And I'm Mother-in-law Christmas.

1167
01:14:46,304 --> 01:14:47,584
Whoa!

1168
01:14:48,904 --> 01:14:50,224
Whoa!

1169
01:14:50,304 --> 01:14:52,704
Hi, Santa!

1170
01:14:52,784 --> 01:14:54,104
Hi, Bud!

1171
01:14:55,544 --> 01:14:57,584
Sylvia.

1172
01:14:58,624 --> 01:15:03,304
Oh, the little pellets behind me?
I'll clean those up later.

1173
01:15:03,384 --> 01:15:06,184
Santa, where do you keep
the Phillips screwdrivers?

1174
01:15:06,264 --> 01:15:08,784
Oh, elf construction. Talk to Irv, OK?

1175
01:15:08,864 --> 01:15:10,224
Oh, oh, Cupid!

1176
01:15:11,584 --> 01:15:14,464
At this altitude you might
consider an underdiaper.

1177
01:15:14,544 --> 01:15:15,904
I don't mind the draught.

1178
01:15:17,064 --> 01:15:19,344
- That was Cupid.
- Yeah.

1179
01:15:19,424 --> 01:15:20,904
Hello, Santa.

1180
01:15:20,984 --> 01:15:24,144
- Father Time.
- Father Time. What next?

1181
01:15:24,224 --> 01:15:26,344
Well, hello, Santa.

1182
01:15:26,424 --> 01:15:28,464
This is a blast!

1183
01:15:28,544 --> 01:15:29,824
Mother Nature.

1184
01:15:31,024 --> 01:15:34,304
- How can I ever thank you for this?
- Oh, don't thank me.

1185
01:15:34,384 --> 01:15:36,504
- He's the one who brought us here.
- Dad.

1186
01:15:36,584 --> 01:15:37,824
Charlie!

1187
01:15:37,904 --> 01:15:39,384
- Hi, Santa!
- Hey, Tooth.

1188
01:15:39,464 --> 01:15:40,984
- Hi, Santa.
- Sandy.

1189
01:15:41,064 --> 01:15:44,504
Checked in with Curtis and found out you
were behind, so I called professionals.

1190
01:15:44,504 --> 01:15:45,384
Checked in with Curtis and found out you
were behind, so I called professionals.

1191
01:15:46,064 --> 01:15:47,504
Uncle Scott!

1192
01:15:48,704 --> 01:15:51,704
- Lucy, what's happened?
- I found her locked in a closet.

1193
01:15:51,784 --> 01:15:52,744
What's wrong?

1194
01:15:52,864 --> 01:15:55,744
You've got to see what Frost
did to my mom and dad.

1195
01:16:11,144 --> 01:16:12,704
It's gonna be OK.

1196
01:16:24,824 --> 01:16:26,024
Yeah, and...?

1197
01:16:26,104 --> 01:16:28,304
Elficers, I have him.

1198
01:16:29,304 --> 01:16:31,464
Jack, this isn't funny.

1199
01:16:31,544 --> 01:16:33,504
Unfreeze the parents right now.

1200
01:16:33,584 --> 01:16:37,304
No way, Claus. I can't unfreeze them
without unfreezing myself,

1201
01:16:37,383 --> 01:16:40,263
and that is something I'll never do.

1202
01:16:41,544 --> 01:16:43,024
Mother Nature, help me out.

1203
01:16:43,104 --> 01:16:45,544
- Can you thaw him out?
- I'm sorry, Santa.

1204
01:16:45,624 --> 01:16:48,104
Our powers don't work
on legendary figures.

1205
01:16:48,184 --> 01:16:50,304
Isn't that a shame?

1206
01:17:08,704 --> 01:17:11,984
- What do you say, Luce?
- Do you think it'll work?

1207
01:17:13,303 --> 01:17:15,864
The question is, do you?

1208
01:17:42,184 --> 01:17:44,464
OK.

1209
01:17:44,544 --> 01:17:47,664
This is what you're all reduced to?

1210
01:17:49,304 --> 01:17:52,263
Sending a little girl in
to save the day, are we?

1211
01:17:53,464 --> 01:17:56,584
What you gonna do, adorablise me?

1212
01:17:56,663 --> 01:17:58,784
Sweet me into submission?

1213
01:17:58,904 --> 01:18:00,784
Cute me to death?

1214
01:18:01,904 --> 01:18:04,343
Make me change my... way!

1215
01:18:05,344 --> 01:18:06,663
Hey.

1216
01:18:06,744 --> 01:18:08,784
I feel so strange.

1217
01:18:10,343 --> 01:18:13,464
It's so gushy inside.

1218
01:18:15,744 --> 01:18:17,144
Do I smell suntan lotion?

1219
01:18:18,023 --> 01:18:19,744
I feel so tropical.

1220
01:18:23,624 --> 01:18:25,944
What's happening to me?

1221
01:18:26,024 --> 01:18:28,183
I'm warming your heart.

1222
01:18:28,264 --> 01:18:30,904
But they told me it couldn't be done.

1223
01:18:30,984 --> 01:18:34,184
But they didn't know
about magical hugs.

1224
01:18:40,744 --> 01:18:41,864
I think I like it.

1225
01:19:02,183 --> 01:19:03,944
Mom, Dad!

1226
01:19:04,024 --> 01:19:05,424
- Lucy!
- Mom! Dad!

